      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["Thin self-supported B-10, thickness approx."
		," 50-mug/cm**2, were used as target."]
	}
      ]
     ,"ADD-RES":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"COMP", "dict":"ADD-RES", "idict":20,"hlp":"Comparison with calculated values"}]
	,"x4freetext":[".The elastic-transfer calculations."
		,"Typical experimental spectra obtained with the MAGSP"
		,"for N-14 and B-10 detected at forward angles is"
		,"reported on fig.1."]
	}
      ]
     ,"COMMENT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["*By authors*.In order to determine a complete angular"
		,"distribution from ANG-CM=16-degree up to ANG-CM=176-"
		,"degree, two different experimental arrangements were"
		,"used. In both cases, the cross sections at forward"
		,"angles ANG-CM more than 100-degree were determined"
		,"by detecting the recoiling target nuclei at forward"
		,"angles.In both experimental setup two silicon detectors"
		,"symmetrically placed at fixed angles with respect to"
		,"the beam direction allowed the normalization of the"
		,"cross sections and the monitoring of the beam direction"]
	}
      ]
     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"TELES", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Counter telescope"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" To detected the reaction products corresponding"
		,"to intermediate angles more than 60-degree and less"
		,"than 120-degree, a 60-cm diameter scattering chamber"
		,"was used. A delta-E(18-mum)-E(100-mum) silicon"
		,"telescope, mounted in the chamber,allowed the detection"
		,"and identification of ions of N-14, elastically"
		,"scattered from the target, as well as the recoiling"
		,"B-10 nuclei and other reaction products."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"MAGSP", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Magnetic spectrometer"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" An Enge split-pole magnetic spectrograph-"
		," for the detection of particles at forward angles (less"
		," than 25-degree)"]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"PS", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Position sensitive detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" Two different gas-filled a position-sensitive"
		,"detectors were used to detect the particles in focal"
		,"plane of the instrument.The first detector was a drift"
		,"chamber, employed to obtain the data for E(lab)=38.1"
		,"and 42 MeV bombarding energies. The second one was"
		,"a hybrid delta-E-E position sensitive detector, which"
		,"used to extract data for E(lab)=46 and 50 MeV"
		,"bombarding energies."]
	}
      ]
     ,"CORRECTION":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":[" The data at each angle were normalized with respect to"
		,"the monitor counts and quantities proportional to"
		,"sigma/sigma(Rutherford) were derived."
		,"The experimental points obtained with the magnetic"
		,"spectrograph were also corrected for the ion charge"
		,"state by using experimental charge distributions"
		,"measured at frequent intervals during the data taking"
		,"period. The data from different experimental setups"
		,"were normalized with respect to each other at a minimum"
		,"of five different angles."]
	}
      ]
     ,"INC-SPECT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["*En-rsl* The position resolution for ions scattered off"
		,"B-10 is typically 2.5-mm which corresponds to an energy"
		,"resolution of approximately 140 keV. The energy"
		,"resolution for recoiling ions is about 250 keV, mostly"
		,"due to multiple scattering in the aluminum absorber."]
	}
      ]
